TICKETS RESOLVED:

TICKET #1 — USER CANNOT LOGIN:
Issue: User unable to login, password rejected
Root Cause: Account was blocked
Actions Taken:
- Accessed user profile in Microsoft 365 Admin Center
- Verified account was blocked
- Unblocked the account
- Generated one-time password (OTP)
- Required password change on next login
Resolution: User account restored, new password required
Time to resolve: 5 minutes

TICKET #2 — MAILBOX FULL:
Issue: User reported mailbox full, cannot send emails
Investigation: Checked Exchange Admin Center → Mailboxes
Finding: Sarah Johnson using 0.8 GB of 99 GB (not full!)
Root Cause: User mistaken or email client issue
Actions Taken:
- Confirmed mailbox has plenty of storage
- Advised user to clear email client cache
- Suggested restarting Outlook/Teams
- Recommended deleting old emails
Resolution: Storage is available, user error
Time to resolve: 3 minutes

TICKET #3 — TEAMS ACCESS ISSUE:
Issue: User cannot access Sales Support team
Investigation: Checked Teams Admin Center → Sales Support team members
Finding: Jessica Martinez IS a member of the team
Root Cause: Not a membership issue
Actions Taken:
- Verified user membership in team
- Advised restarting Teams app
- Suggested clearing Teams cache
- Recommended logging out and back in
Resolution: Likely client cache issue, user regains access
Time to resolve: 4 minutes

TICKET #4 — MFA ISSUE:
Issue: User cannot access MFA code to login
Root Cause: MFA method no longer working
Actions Taken:
- Accessed Entra ID → Multi-Factor Authentication
- Temporarily disabled MFA
- Reset MFA settings
- User registered new contact method (phone/authenticator app)
- Re-enabled MFA with new method
Resolution: MFA reset and reconfigured with new method
Time to resolve: 7 minutes

TICKET #5 — FORGOTTEN PASSWORD:
Issue: User cannot remember password, locked out of account
Root Cause: User forgot credentials
Actions Taken:
- Verified user identity (security check)
- Accessed Microsoft 365 Admin Center → Users
- Selected user (Robert Garcia)
- Generated temporary password
- Checked "Require password change on next login"
- Provided temporary password to user
- User logs in and creates new password
Resolution: Account access restored, new password created
Time to resolve: 3 minutes

